  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "minor",
    "intended": "Let $\\mathrm{ex}_r(n;K_{r+1}^r)$ be the maximum number of $r$-edges that can be placed on $n$ vertices without forming a $K_{r+1}^r$ (the $r$-uniform complete graph on $r+1$ vertices).\n\nIs every $r$-hypergraph $G$ on $n$ vertices the union of at most $\\mathrm{ex}_{r}(n;K_{r+1}^r)$ many copies of $K_r^r$ and $K_{r+1}^r$, no two of which share a $K_r^r$?",
